PKI(Public Key Infrastructure) - 


PKCS 7 - is a way to store Certificate as individual files.

PKCS 12 - stores Certificate and private key as a package

X.509 - 


CRL(Certificate revocation list) - is a path,

CRL is correct. CRL, which can take up to 24 hours to react to a bad certificate, 
is starting to fade because OCSP can identify issues in close to real-time.


OCSP(Online Certificate Status Protocol) - is more modern version of Certificate revocation list